      "content": "A surgical firewall rule sounds better, but I need to be 100% sure before I sign off on that. If we try this \"fix\" and it fails to actually stop the injection, the board is going to come for my head for not just doing the full shutdown. \n\nBe honest with me—on a scale of 1 to 10, how confident are you that a firewall rule is actually going to block this specific exploit? Is there even a real chance we're just delaying the inevitable and making a bad situation worse? I need to know if the vulnerability is truly \"critical\" or if we can safely manage it without the outage.",
